    Scope and Contents
Hamlin recalls his years working in the coal mines of Illinois and discusses mine operations and structures, mine conditions, hazards, union activities, wages and working hours, black lung disease, and relations between miners. 1 tape, 29 mins., 17 pp. 
Interview by H. Dean Campbell, 1972 
